    p I've been working remote for most of life. During the past couple of years I've spent most of my time traveling around Asia, including Japan, Korea, Hong Kong, and now most recently Taiwan. I've always enjoyed reviewing places on Google Maps, but started maintaining my own collection of "good places to work from" and eventually turned it into this site, Cafe and Cowork.
    p For me, the most important factors are comfortable seats, a quiet environment, power outlets, and stable wifi. Those are the main things I need to get work done, but of course it's also nice if there is good food and cheap drinks.
    p On the tech-side, this website is mostly static content. To keep things as simple as possible, there is no database, just a markdown/yaml file for each cafe. The server is built with node.js, using express, and pages are rendered server-side using `pug` (my view engine of choice) with vanilla CSS (no boilerplate).
